com.paydiant.android.core.domain

Class DeleteDevice

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paydiant.android.core.domain.DeleteDevice

  • public class DeleteDevice
extends Object
    This class provides information about the device that needs to be unlinked. Use the DeleteDevice(ContextWrapper) constructor to create the delete device object, unless there is a specific requirement to set deviceId and/or deviceTypeName properties to have special values than the default.

    The deviceId property's default value would be the unique device Id, which is retrieved through DevicePropertyUtil.retrieveDeviceProperties(contextWrapper).get(DevicePropertyUtil.DEVICE_ID). The deviceTypeName property will have "android" as its default value.

    See Also:
    DevicePropertyUtil
